social_posts.post_text: God I was cranky painting tonight and while I painted through it I realized that  part of the problem Is I’m getting crowded.  Between me and my nook, my paintings and my all my frames as well as all my stuff because after all it’s my bedroom It’s getting too much.  I hate that im getting attic thoughts.  Feels like doom to a painting….To land  in the attic Is like a paintings coffin.  organizing tomorrow maybe it’ll be better.
Much better mood today. Organized as predicted.  I’m starting to stock pile 8x10”s for a local festival I’m in at end of the month

I was trying to do that caption thing to the music.  But I only got “oh” Which seems fitting.  So Follow the “oh” to all the available people I painted this month.  Message me if one is giving you your own ”oh” vibe.  I’m heading out of town Monday but can mail before I go.
Millie bird. Queen of stare downs.
This is why people are so addicting to paint. I think I would normally keep going, but there’s something about him that just kind of made me stop, so I did - not up to me
The paint over that got  messier and messier. (See story). Shoulda left it.  UPDATE.  HEADING  TO JOIN A FEW FRIENDS IN DURHAM, NC
Scrolling through while waiting in a waiting room.  Shoulda left this one alone.

Returned home to some new prints waiting for me!!! I’m bringing them with me to the festival next weekend.  But if you want to snag yours prior.  Go for it!  They are 8x10.  Professionally printed on heavy weight art paper. $20 each.  FREE domestic shipping. International shipping possible but will be cost more.  Shoot me a message!

When I was home with my parents I actually tried  to paint a tiny painting in my old bedroom but  was so afraid that I’d  get paint everywhere so I quit early on because  I knew  I would’ve gotten paint everywhere - then I tried to actually paint on the plane and that was no good and about five minutes In I realized  it was ridiculous to even try - then I came home to my nook. Which seemed like ages ago I was here but really wasn’t that all long ago and after all that gibberish this is where I landed after I dragged my “tired but oh so need to paint” self.  24x30
Someone  that ended so simply when there was nothing simple about getting here.  Feel this one a lot. (A16x20 paint over)
Little messy guy who looks likes he’s melting.

Some days when I paint it feels like the first time even though obviously it’s not.  But please please please I hope the joy I feel when I finally sit to paint never leaves me.  Ps.  I ran a mile today. (8x10)
held my breath til the Commission arrived.  Arrived.

In the beginning, she actually reminded me of Marie-Antoinette and now I have no idea  8x10.  For any of the locals I’ll be at lazy daze  this weekend. I’ve been pretty slack about picking who goes with me. But I’ll be there….Sweating

If I were to title this it would  be. “I’m sorry mom”. This lady was the other lady from a few years back that was living in a sealed box in my attic. (It turned out to be  too much to ship so I just brought her back home and left her in the attic.  I finally yanked the  box  out - Anyhow I was telling my mother this story.  She asked to see the original painting .  I flipped the camera and She Says. “Oh erica.  Don’t.  I love the colors.” I said don’t worry mom. I’ll just tweek her.  I’ll leave the colors.  I kinda at least did that.
Hello from the woods.
Not where I was expecting to go.  I had other ideas.  But so did the painting.  So I stepped aside.  24 inches x 36 inches
Tonight I took the lead.
I sat in front of a computer for far too long today.  Finally I got to paint.  Tonight.  This one.  Working through the near empty tubes. Still.
It’s not quite time but I’m packing up two of these guys tomorrow and I wanted them to have their “wall moment” with their monthly family.
My little basket of nubbies. (Per story) got a little less but damn it the basket ain’t empty.
He ate my cheery pinks and yellows.
The only thing I could muster after a good night out.  Tackled that one not too far back that was driving me  mad since.
Mr Saturday night will  turn  into Ms dry Sunday  and we’ll see what happens.
Tonight. I stuck it out.  16x20

Throwing some of the bigger guys to the sales floor.  They could barely get in the photo.  So scroll for Individual shots.  They are each 18x24 inches Tomorrow will be the 16x20’s.  Message me for prices or more photos.
Tonight.  I reeled it up.
A paint over.  I stopped when I saw that sweet face.  But Before that she reminded me of a guy who I played quarters with way back.
You don’t know how badly I wanted to fill up that space with a big giant head.  But she kept me from doing so. 12x12 in honor of those who have fallen to my sales floor

My lady had a shining moment last night. I stood beside her at a loss for words while she took the glory of being awarded first place at the Wilson Arts Center Juried art show.  When I heard my name, I wont lie, for a split second, I wanted to run, then I thought of my daughters standing beside me thinking this is good for them to see, then I felt guilty because there was so much amazing art and then I had to just deal and let whats to happen, actually happen. Kind of like my whole approach to painting.  So I did and that’s when I really got to soak up all the magic that followed. Talking art, meeting other artists, being apart of something and ultimately feeling really really proud, I have gotten so many no’s along the way and so many more are to come but this yes was a grand slam/super bowl kind of yes and I am so grateful for  it but truly none of it would have happened without the friendships I have made along the way. The comments, the likes, the shares, and of course the people who wanted my people to hang in their homes, all of it has been the fuel to keep me going so truly thank you because I need to keep going.
PS …of course I had to paint when I got home

Serious battle with this one.  A paint over that I wish I captured along the way but I didn’t.  Every time I thought I was done and did that last stroke.  I’d feel something else and off we went.  Now I’m just feeling tired.
Trust me we looked nothing like this ten minutes ago.  Two days in and this is where we landed. Throwing the brushes down. 16x20 inches. - TOTALLY AVAILABLE
The last song playing in my ears when we said done.  This is the guy that I knew wasn’t done when I did the reel  of the stages a few days ago. - TOTALLY AVAILABLE
Some people get lucky and get to hang in my living room as part of the decor til they find their people.  20x20 and available.
This one  Last night I painted over someone I should have let be and after nearly three hours I hand swiped it and went to bed.  No hand swipe tonight .  18x24 inches. - Totally available.

All of these guys have been on the floor at some point.  Still at it, Still available and Still decent price.  All under $250.  Almost got ugly when I stood on the stool to take the photo and realized the ceiling fan was still whipping.  Message me.
It’s rainy rainy rainy.  But I have a new batch on the floor looking for a wall.  Swipe for mug shots.  Message me for sweet price and more photos.
From last tonight to tonight.  8x10

This is me walking to see bunches of my paintings for the first time all lit up.  Everything about the walk felt so good.  Dark.  Rainy.  Windy.  Solo.  Taking it all in.  If anyone local is kicking down 96 (downtown Zebulon) check it out at the Old Debnam hardware store.  In color of course.  I just got all sorts of arty with this one.  Also Big big gigantically big shout out to my friend and town commissioner Shannon Baxter for having the vision and making this happen.
Painting in my childhood bedroom all while trying not to get paint on anything Kind of made me feel like a child again.
As far as I got last night.
My last night in my old room and I found myself crying at the end.

My month of people.  Here’s to bulk of September.  Some feel like forever ago.  All are available but one. I’ll try and post photos in my stories but in the meantime message me if one is talking to you.
Was going to tackle mr Monday from last night but instead I created little miss Tuesday.
The guy I intended to paint over tonight Mysteriously disappeared.  I gave up looking for him and went with this newbie.  Loaded and Messy.  Let the poor guy dry
She’s this close to a hand swipe.  Til we meet again.  And we so will.

I finally got back to mr Monday.  Bugged me all week.  Just like the grocery store lady who watched me like a hawk just because I missed the eggs at self check out.  Pure accident and I know she was  just doing her job.  But still rubbed wrong when she reached into my bag to rescan them and then never left.  Mind you I’ve been going to this store every damn day practically for years. #ventover. #ifeelbetter
At the market. (North Carolina museum of art) If any of these catch your eye and you want it, just message me. Everything here is under $250 with frame (shipping not included).
Scary Mary on the 8th of October but really was the 7th. My dads birthday.
Little miss mighty came out of no where and had something to say.
I picked her tonight to paint over.  Then couldn’t.  So didn’t.
I have been painting the same canvas over and over again for the last two days while I process what I can’t process.
null
A paint over that looks a little smug about it.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
See ya to the sweet girl who I didn’t like at all from a week or so ago.  Had her.  Lost her.  ended up with her.  I call a truce.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
I won’t lie. I dragged myself to paint tonight.  UPDATE.  HE DIDN’T STICK AROUND LONG.  HOW CAN I BLAME HIM WHEN PALM BEACH WAS CALLING.
I’ve been painting these two for way too long. Im releasing them.  Not because I feel like they are done but because im done with them.  24x30 and moving on. TOTALLY AVAILABLE
Finally returned to the creepy William Defoe guy from a ways back.  I also drove through the worst rain storm after seeing the taylor movie.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
Um….So much paint for such a little guy.  UPDATE but  New Mexico doesn’t care.  He’s off to a great collector!

that one stoke gets me every time.  It’s either magic or it’s destruction.  I had magic.  Then I had destruction.  And then I built myself back to here.  Now just pausing before we go through it all over again.
I’ma feeling this guys worry about being the paint over.
Totally absorbed all that I was feeling.

She actually made it through me tweeking without completing becoming a paint over.  Good day.  Complete with a thrift store haul….a little lamp who’s only purpose is to give that chill ambience.  And a narrow wire basket for my paint.  But my paint looks like it’s in jail.  So I’ll have rethink the  baskets purpose.  Scroll to see.

Damn you gun man who forever changed my Maine. Damn you.  You altered the course for so many.  Little kids are going to bed tonight scared.  Grown ups are going to bed tonight scared  People are weeping in their beds tonight.  Damn you.

So ….I ordered some frames for a local exhibit.  But I got too big of frames and now I can’t use them.  These guys are all 12x12 inches Framed I think they come under 17x17 inches.  If you want one.  I’ll include the frame.  They are gold. $300 with frame.  Free domestic shipping.  I can send oversees but have to charge extra but I’ll still send the frame.  DM MOI

I found this song while walking in the woods not too long ago.  Been walking in the woods a lot recently.  I’m lucky I can because underneath this big giant sky that we all share so many can’t go walking in the woods.  So here are my people  from October. Some left me already but these guys are All available and no one is priced more than a fancy dinner out.  Depending on how you define “fancy” ;)
I couldn’t help myself.  I had to paint one of those four frames.  Now I’m curious… which one do you like better?

This one. Perhaps it’s me but I’m getting a real disappointment feeling.  So Im calling it because six personalities and two days is enough.  Also while I’m here.  Thanks so much for the feedback for the gold versus grey frame yesterday.  I personally liked The Grey for her.  But I still have three other gold frames to work with.
Commissions are tricky.  I’ll forever be traumatized by that very first one.  They mailed it back. (This guy is heading west). 18x24 inches

First photo.  What or rather… who I painted tonight.  Second photo.  My 25 cent thrift store thingy.  Don’t know what it is.  But instead of swiping my brushes against the wall as I have.  I now use this mystery thing hanging from another thrift store find….A fish hook that is now pretty much camouflaged.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
Im totally good with the time change.  Um…Darker earlier???. Yes please.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
Sacrificed one to get to him.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
I won’t lie.  When I look at this I want to go dark.  But pink ruled.  20x20 inches.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE
Stuck her in a frame so I could  stop painting.  Voila.  UPDATE.  SHES KEEPING TO CAROLINA ROOTS.  FOUND HER HOME IN CHARLOTTE.
The only energy I had was to change the background.
Don’t know where this guy came from but slamming the pause button before he morphs into someone else. 16x20

I have always loved carrot soup. And butternut squash soup.  But Today I have a new soup girlfriend.  Pumpkin ginger soup!!!’ Oh my god.. It had mango and peanut butter in it.  I texted it to my sister and my best friend and now to my friends of instagram. (Slide for the recipe). Im a terrible cook but this made me feel like a superstar.
I worked from my basket of nubbies in hopes I’d go through a few.  I didn’t.
Yesterday i took the paintings down to stack them and count them.  Then woke up this morning and didn’t know what to look at.  #eerie
Im definitely throwing her on the wall. Because come tomorrow morning I want to figure out who she reminds me of.  16x20 inches
I Kept painting around that left eye that was giving me @snoopdogg vibes but  I still lost the dogg vibe.
I went to get something to eat.  When I came back I couldn’t keep going.  16x20 inches
City girl tonight.
Bringing Mr Maine back to Miss North Carolina.
Mr New Jersey in a hotel bathroom
Home and I brought these beauties back with me.  I literally waited my whole life for the painting that lived in a closet.  Now it’s time to figure out who painted it.
Nothing like a full moon on a cold night with naked trees. Heading outside.
At one point she was reminded me of someone I worked with long ago when I was a dishwasher.  She was soft  and sweet.  I wish I snapped a picture before I lost her.  18x24 inches

Here’s the story of this one.  I broke my rule.  I painted over someone else’s painting.  I bought it at goodwill with full intention just to use the frame.  Til I couldn’t  separate the two.  Then it sat in its original form for a long time. And  in a weak moment when I had no other canvasses And none of my own I wanted to paint over.  I came  back to the gingerbread people.  And painted over it.  From Then on I was cursed.  And rightfully so, Because it was SOOO MANY people that I never felt.  Tonight I was in the same boat.  No canvasses and no one I wanted to paint over.  So this one and I went at it again.  Honestly I don’t like it so much but I like the idea that I’m moving on.  Lesson learned.

It’s been a month already and here I am with my November people.  Some already left me.  But I added them at the end anyway so I can look back to see the whole family.  All on the wall are available as always.  Ps.  I ended up never painting the wall and just added more nail holes
I’m kind of digging them in their own little way.  So I’m letting them sit.
I think I stumbled upon my first diptych.
Well that’s a double first  A horizontal landscape/ish that came out of no where.
If I were to remember anything of this day.  I’d remember my mother opening her front door to show me the first snow fall.
A paint over that gained a creepy friend.  It wasn’t til I snapped the photo did I realize creepy friend looks like it’s in a straight jacket.  18x24 inches
Final guy to the reel.
I was so into painting her I accidentally squirted a huge blob of paint on my phone.  I am also very tired.  Both legit.  But here she is and joining her new 12x12 friends.
The start of 16x20s… available.  Message me for more photos.  I have frames too.
8x8.  Weird size.  I only bought the canvas for the Frame.  Turns out Canvas slightly too big for the frame.  Totally available

An early start to another round of available 16x20s.  Some old some sorta old some new.  And two I think I’ll be eventually painting over or adding to if no one snags them.  Same old deal.  Message me.  I’ll show you a better photo and framed. .
Round three of 16x20’s available.  Hustle bustle on to the next batch. Again.  Message me and I’ll shoot you a better photo amongst my mess.
He has a box to go with him.  Bigger pieces coming tomorrow. .24x30
The start of the 18x24 crew that is available.
And the start of last of last night….. 24x30. Update.  I couldn’t go back in after all .  TOTALLY AVAILABLE.
I knew I wouldn’t go back to yesterday.  Instead I painted over an old canvas I found in the attic searching for lost decorations that I still can’t find.  16x20
Went to a Christmas Parade today .  And I always cry a little bit at parades. But today When the marching band went by I just couldn’t stop.

My sweet mother who is always concerned about  the paint on my hardwood Floors called me tonight worried about me crying at parades.  I cry because parades are sweet.  Community coming  together.  Kids waving.  Mom and dad’s waving. It’ll get me every time.  24x20. TOTALLY AVAILABLE.

While looking for decorations in the attic a few days ago, I found another old canvas and pulled  it out and stuck it behind  a chair in the hallway. I must’ve stuck it in the attic as an out of sight out of mind thing.  when I had no canvases tonight and didn’t want to paint over anybody, I then remembered the 24x36 canvas behind the chair.  TOTALLY AVAILABLE.

2 minutes to spare.  Off I go to watch my nieces and nephew sing Christmas carols live in Chicago .  Live like you tube live!!! Mr ultra itty bitty at 4x4.  Available to anyone who wants him. $40.  UODATE.  HES HEADING TO THE CITY…NYC.
I snuck her in tonight.  Ssssshhhh.
I didn’t have a whole Lot of time tonight, but I so needed to paint.  12x12.
He wouldn’t look at me.  16x20.
One became two and then things got dark.  8x10
And that’s just about a wrap 2023. Lots of wrap ups out there and Here’s mine….A personal fave from each month.
Turns out she was the last one of 23.
Half holiday/Half home.  Back from holidays and finished  this guy in my foreign nook.. I had full intention to say more but I’m wiped. Full on drool.
The way they change and surprise me is what gets me every time like it’s the first time.  12x12

Remember the orange lady in my story the other day that was driving me mad?  She has turned into a man that I like better.  For now anyway.  I also played  the “Bob Ross: Art of Chill Board Game” that I discovered in the hallway of my friends house. Nothing chill about it.  Confusing as hell.  Poor bob Ross.
Swirling whirling fighting circles with this one. Everyone before him felt empty.  16x20 inches.  Totally available
One of yesterday’s characters who became Mr orange man.
Cranky alll day.  Tomorrow I’m dragging my self outside for a long long walk.
Painted over one that was driving me nuts. Feeling less nuts about it now.  11x14.
This whole big  mess of a thing  has every bit of me in it.  I needed to get lost In A painting.  And that I did.  Several times.  24x36 inches.  Not a paint over.
I feel like this guy won the fight.  20x20 inches.
He needs to dry and I need to warm up.  8x10
For two days they had a partner.  I left his fingers on the right.  So damn messy.  20x20 inches

I got a voice mail today from someone I hadn’t talked to in a few years. They didn’t know if I was alive or misplaced. I called them back to report that I was Alive and misplaced.  Oddly this guy kind of looks like him.  12x12
Completely on his own.  I was there but was distracted by my own thoughts.  16x20.
